      "automation_source": "clawsweeper",
      "repair_reason": "A narrow automated repair can move repair constraint selection into the per-candidate fallback path and add one mixed-runtime regression test.; Needs attention: The diff changes cron tool-execution boundaries and still applies repair constraints based on the previous runtime rather than the actual fallback candidate.; Review finding: [P2] Constrain repair options per fallback candidate — src/cron/isolated-agent/run-... (sha=c126925fd90966271b69437f3931ccf39cf1bf4a)",
      "review_summary": "The PR adds cron empty-sanitized-output repair/fail-loud handling, CLI bundled-MCP suppression and session reuse, descendant-output recovery, sender-ownership coverage, and focused regression tests.\n\nReproducibility: yes. The current-main bug is source-reproducible from empty synthesized text returning null in delivery finalization, and the PR-head blocker is source-reproducible from runWithModelFallback invoking per-candidate callbacks while repair options are shared.",
